  "prompt": "Are marks of pre-board exams added up to calculate the CGPA of X class?",
  "response": "No, the marks of pre-board exams are not added up to calculate the CGPA (Cumulative Grade Point Average) for Class X in most educational systems, including CBSE (Central Board of Secondary Education) in India. Pre-board exams are typically conducted by schools as a practice or preparatory test for the actual board exams. They are meant to help students prepare for the final board exams by simulating the exam environment and identifying areas for improvement.\n\nThe CGPA for Class X is calculated based on the grades obtained in the final board exams (or internal assessments, depending on the board's grading system). Pre-board exam scores are not considered in this calculation. However, performing well in pre-boards can boost a student's confidence and readiness for the actual board exams, indirectly impacting their final grades. Always refer to your specific board's guidelines for precise information.",
